													<div class="" style="border-color: #c2d9e7;"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="word-wrap: break-word; table-layout: fixed;"><tbody><tr><td style="padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; border-bottom: 0px none #cccccc; color: #000000; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size: 11px;">
<div>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
		<span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;"><strong>CONNECT: End of Life and End of Support</strong></span></span></p>
</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">The CONNECT reading software was last updated in 2009. Since that time, software and meter reading technology have evolved considerably, as have customer expectations. Since the last CONNECT update, Badger Meter has introduced many new products which are not supported in CONNECT, including ORION<sup><span style="font-size: 7px;">®</span></sup> Cellular, Fixed Network (SE) and Migratable (ME) endpoints, HR-E</span><sup><span style="font-size: 7px;"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 7px;">®</span></span></span></sup><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">and HR-E LCD high-resolution encoders, high resolution E-Series<sup><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 7px;">®</span></span></sup> Ultrasonic meters, and the new ORION Field Application 4.0.0 handheld route reading software.</span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">Additionally, feedback from customers indicates that it is increasingly difficult to find support for the Microsoft operating software supported by CONNECT. For these reasons, Badger Meter is announcing the CONNECT software end of life. Effective immediately, Badger Meter will no longer renew CONNECT software maintenance agreements. Customers with active CONNECT maintenance agreements will continue to receive technical support until the term of their current service agreement expires. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">With this announcement, please use this opportunity to contact your utility customers and present the value of upgrading from CONNECT to BEACON<sup><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 7px;">®</span></span></sup> AMA or ReadCenter<sup><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 7px;">®</span></span></sup> Analytics Mobile. Upgrade options include:</span></p>
<ul><li>
		<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">BEACON AMA - please contact Marketing for pricing and timing</span>.</li>
	<li>
		<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">ReadCenter Analytics Mobile – utilize Software Upgrade Marketing Program RDC-MP-00770, which is located on the <a href="http://www.badgermeter.com/Media-Center/Pricing-Incentive-Programs/Marketing-Programs1.htm" style="color: #0000FF!important;">Badger Meter extranet</a></span>.</li>
	<li>
		<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">Unused fees paid for CONNECT software maintenance agreements may be applied towards a utility’s reading data management software upgrade at the time of software transiton.</span>
</li>
	<li>
		<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">Should a customer initially deploy ReadCenter Analytics Mobile and later wish to migrate to BEACON AMA, licensing fees paid now will be taken into consideration when BEACON AMA pricing is established.</span>
</li>
</ul><p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">A list of end utility customers with CONNECT software deployments will be provided to all sales support managers for distribution to the remainder of the direct and distributor sales managers.</span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana,geneva,sans-serif;">If you have any questions about this information, please contact <a href="mailto:kanderson@badgermeter.com?subject=CONNECT%20EOL" style="color: #0000FF!important;">Kristie Anderson</a>.</span></p>
